  "text": "Historically, the cultural representations and images of impairments were associated with distortion, ugliness, and a threat to humanness and selfhood. Its occurrence was explained in terms of divine punishment, karma or immorality [CITATION_1] (Shakespeare, , 2006 . According to Kreigel (1987) , the disabled were conceptualized as \"others\" and \"creatures\" devoid of selfhood. People with disabilities represented a strange and dark world, and the society of the \"normal\" individuals lived in fear of \"demonic cripples\" (p. 33).",
